==English==

===Noun===

'''katabatic wind'''

# Any wind blowing down an [[incline]]; the [[opposite]] of [[anabatic wind]]. If the wind is [[warm]], it is called a [[foehn]]; if [[cold]], it may be a [[fall wind]] (such as the [[bora]]), or a [[gravity wind]] (such as a [[mountain wind]]).

